<font color="#FF0000">REMEMBER WHY WE DO CELEBRATE</font><br>
<tt>Tue Nov 11  2:11:48 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
A couple of thoughts:<br><br>
--We won't watch Brave Heart again because of the way violence is portrayed.  It simply does not interest us.<br><br>
--It is now Veteran's Day, and we should remember those who died before their time, so that we can &quot;discuss&quot; things on this site, and generally go about our daily business.  I, this year, will especially remember Al Avery, Jim Thomas, Steve Northern, Randy McComb and Duane Hackney.  You who are new to this site won't know these name, but these people are the ones we should be celebrating in our movies.<br><br>
Take care everyone.  Happy Veteran's Day!  HooYa!!
